<dedicat align="l"><hi r="italic">For Chet Baker</hi></dedicat>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">You stepped through</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">the Van Gogh blue curtain</l>
<l ln="3        ">into my dream.</l>
<l ln="4        ">That day in Paris,</l>
<l ln="5        ">we sat at the outdoor caf&eacute; for hours.</l>
<l ln="6        ">I had high breasts</l>
<l ln="7        ">and my dress was cut low.</l>
<l ln="8        ">You leaned close to me, so close;</l>
<l ln="9        ">yet, did not touch.</l>
<l ln="10      ">&ldquo;I don't need to,&rdquo; you said, &ldquo;it's the dope,</l>
<l ln="11      ">it's the rush</l>
<l ln="12      ">so much better than lust.</l>
<l ln="13      ">Hush, take a deep breath</l>
<l ln="14      ">and you'll just go to sleep like I did.&rdquo;</l>
<l ln="15      ">I knew you were hustling me,</l>
<l ln="16      ">that underneath the hipster philosophy</l>
<l ln="17      ">lay the same old Chet out to score.</l>
<l ln="18      ">Still, I lent you money, still I followed you</l>
<l ln="19      ">to the pissoir,</l>
<l ln="20      ">where Lucien gave you &ldquo;le fix.&rdquo;</l>
<l ln="21      ">Shaking his head, he pocketed the money and said,</l>
<l ln="22      ">&ldquo;I heard you were dead,&rdquo;</l>
<l ln="23      ">and you answered, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo;</l>
<l ln="24      ">You said when you slammed into the pavement,</l>
<l ln="25      ">Amsterdam shook, then settled back into apathy,</l>
<l ln="26      ">the way we all do, when we are through</l>
<l ln="27      ">with the foolishness of living.</l>
<l ln="28      ">You ended up sharing your works with a whore</l>
<l ln="29      ">who waited outside the pissoir door,</l>
<pb n="68">
<l ln="30      ">your generosity as pathetic</l>
<l ln="31      ">as it was predictable.</l>
<l ln="32      ">You wanted sainthood like everybody else.</l>
<l ln="33      ">Instead, you earned the wings</l>
<l ln="34      ">that were too late to save you,</l>
<l ln="35      ">but not too late to raise you</l>
<l ln="36      ">up to junkie heaven.</l>
<l ln="37      ">Later, we stood on the steps of Notre Dame.</l>
<l ln="38      ">You were calm, as you pointed to the bell tower.</l>
<l ln="39      ">You said you saw Quasimodo up there,</l>
<l ln="40      ">holding Esmeralda over the edge</l>
<l ln="41      ">by her hair,</l>
<l ln="42      ">but all I saw staring down were the gargoyles</l>
<l ln="43      ">who'd found peace,</l>
<l ln="44      ">because it meant nothing to them.</l>
<l ln="45      ">&ldquo;I see,&rdquo; I lied, to please you,</l>
<l ln="46      ">but you knew and you blew me a kiss.</l>
<l ln="47      ">You wished me &ldquo;bonne chance,&rdquo;</l>
<l ln="48      ">then you eased into flight,</l>
<l ln="49      ">as the cool, jazzy, starry night</l>
<l ln="50      ">opened its arms to retrieve you.</l></poem>
</div2>
